message: Adds cylayer and ccyzone to docstring of AtomGroup.select_atoms
validating dimensions for self.pbc and addition of discription to docstring
Merge branch 'XDRclean' into develop Merged and finished converting the code to use libxdrfile2

analysis.align: streamlined rms_fit_trj() and alignto()  use common 'select' interface - consistent usage of 'mobile' and 'reference' set - fasta2select() returns dict with 'mobile' and 'reference' keys (MIGHT BREAK OLD   CODE ... but I don't think anyone used this) - the common select code _process_selection() has a hack to accept the old   'target' key instead of 'mobile' until 0.8 - test cases: added unit test for rmsd() and had to adjust the value for   the rms_fit_trj() test case (not really sure why but at least it's consistent   with what VMD shows)
fixed bug in x3dna trj analysis
Added CHANGELOG entry for ten2eleven centerOfMass camelcase fix.
A few errors in code corrected
Trajectory API: optional attribute 'compressed' defined and streamlined guess_format() by introducing get_ext()
altered XYZReader class to not use format  also added unit tests for simple and compressed XYZ files (files in tests/data and comments)
Fixed compatibility with Python2.6. Positional argument specifiers can't be omitted in Python2.6.
Adds test to check for no warning when topology with MW atom type is loaded
Remove any self calls from load method  to make it nice and static
Upated CHANGELOG  brought back the old ContactAnalysis class
Test and docstring cleanup - numpy style docs  - renamed a few methods  - @staticmethod annotation in tests
reduced precision for distance tests from default to 5 decimals so that they also pass on 32 bit
prepare 0.7.0 release: set release and date
AtomGroup.bond(): renamed keyword minimage to pbc for consistency
use sensible warnings when only a header is written

Removed the problem where t0 was ignored. Changed the organisation of the functions and used mroe consistent variable names. Removed the mention of parallel selection which was not implemented. Inlined the function which did not do much.
Updated the UnitTests pertaining to Issue 224.
Changed Timestep constructor to only accept integer argument (defines size of Timestep)
Split out Timestep tests into own file
Trajectory API: partial implementation of Reader.__getitem__()
Generate authors.py from AUTHORS for the tests
fixed AdK testcase: dt and totaltime was broken by fix for Issue 64 - dt is not rounded anymore  hence dt is reported as 0.99999 and not 1.0 - use assert_almost_equal() in test case

Added ENT file extension to PDBReader  Writer and Parser. Updated tests to check succesful loading of PDB file from ENT extension. Updated CHANGELOG  allowed for reading of .ent files in testsuite  shortened '.ent' testfile. Updated docs to show ent extension supported by trajectory readers/writers and topology parser. Changed name of truncated ENT test file to reflect testing purpose.
Changed to non-pythonic symmetric distance matrix assignment
Add missing Lennard van der Felzt in AUTHORS
Added tests for compressed PDB file seeking and reading
Example script for using GNM analysis
Issue 724 - Removing assert statments from test units

Move changelog into to new version
ensure HEADER and TITLE occur just once in a PDB file

added tests for exception raise in GROParser
correct reading/writing of DCD unit cell information (fixes Issue 187)

Added zero-based indices for donors and acceptors in HBond Analysis  updated docs to reflect change. Added deprecation warning for the 1-based index.
Version number set to 0.9.2  date in CHANGELOG updated and Documentation regenerated
docs for PDBQST format integrated into online docs
changed generic Exceptions to specific ones in DCD module
updated MDAnalysis paper citation: published online http://dx.doi.org/10.1002/jcc.21787   also added HELANAL citation and made everything look similar to the googlecode home page
online docs: link to Selection exporters from start page and made exporter table clearer
notes on using Apple gcc and possible problems running examples from source dir (thanks to Justin Lemkul for the tips)

removed tests related to permissive PDBReader

Fixed MPI fork() warning when importing MDAnalysis after MPI_Init() call

HELANAL helix analysis (integrated Ben Hall's Python implementation) - Ben's code is licensed under the GPL v2+ - http://www.ccrnp.ncifcrf.gov/users/kumarsan/HELANAL/helanal.html - reference: Bansal M  Kumar S  Velavan R.  HELANAL - A program to   characterise helix geometry in proteins. J Biomol Struct Dyn. 2000  17(5):811-9. - requires universe and start and stop residue of the helix to be analyzed    write a number of output files - not fully tested! - numpified  removed support code for vector handling and trajectory I/O   (now all done with numpy or MDAnalysis)  added docs
new attributes for universe.trajectory: frame and time - report the frame number and time of the current time step - single frame formats return frame = 0 and time = 0.0 - added test cases
added original HELANAL (Python) code by Benjamin Hall - LICENCE: not free  DO NOT DISTRIBUTE yet - not integrated  this is the code as provided by Ben
AtomGroup.dihedral(): use faster numpy functions to calculate dihedral  added test cases for dihedral() and the phi()/psi()/omega() selection methods
added forgotten CHANGELOG entry (from the Release073 wiki notes)
release 0.7.3 (only changed release number and CHANGELOG)
regenerated online docs with sphinx (changes to align examples)
parser/coordinate entry points: FIXED: would not allow building of psf-only universe (but now issue a warning)
fixed parsing of PDB header data for PrimitivePDBReader (closes #332)
Added PSA module  updates to sphinx RSTs (not compiled).
Removed use of Residue.name and Segment.id
Structural superpositions (analysis.align) can use incomplete matches
H-bonding analysis now defaults to updating selections each time step (fixes Issue 138)

Update all tests to use MDAnalysisTests tempdir

release 0.6.4 (no code changes relative to 0.6.4-rc1  only docs)
Re-link to gro.bz2 files in setup.py

fixed Issue 59 (naveen.michaudagrawal) -- DCDWriter now checks input coordinate array for continguousness - Because DCD's store the data in fortran format  ie a single timestep is (x x x ...  y y y...  z z z...) and through the magic of numpy arrays that's usually transparently handled.
changed the default offset for ProgressMeter
Added new property-based unit test  test_written_remarks_property()  which reveals that DCDFile is not able to handle writing when an empty REMARKS string is provided.
ENH: added py3 compatibility for block_import.
DCDWriteTestRandom now pins down the random seed for testing robustness.
Version changed to 0.9.1 and doc regenerated

New: selection can write snapshot to a pdb file (EXPERIMENTAL) - added a simple PDB writer that does not require Bio.PDB (should rewrite PDBWriter) - added core.util for helper functions like filename mangling - small steps towards a unified trajectory API:   . universe.trajectory points to the reader object   . coord.__init__ advertises readers  writers in dicts
Diagonal elements in contact-matrix are always true
Python 3 compatibility (still likely to break other tests)
fixed imports on Tinker coordinate reader and topology parser

added DCD regression tests against data from old DCDReader

Fixed docstrings for fixes now that copying to standard library dir is no longer needed.
Added notes to CHANGELOG on how to survive API changes (#415)
current_frame variable is now updated in write method of DCDFile.
DCDFile now allows overwriting  based on feedback in PR#1155.
ENH: Added proper DCDFile remarks / header string handling -- all unit tests now pass in python 2.7 & 3.5

Can calculate the distance array without minimum image by setting bpx=None. This makes sense when working on RMS-fitted trajectories which do not obey the original PBC any more. This code avoids having to use a stupid hack like box = 2*box and is perhaps 25% faster by leaving out minimage() This corresponds to r71 in /code/MDAnalysis.
switched sphinx theme to alabaster with MDAnalysis styling
Patched issue with frame iteration in test_coord_match -- all unit tests now pass.
MDAnalysisTestData: only data for tests (separated from the library). See Issue 28 for details.
Added ability to read XYZ files without topology file

regenerated docs (fixed Issue 127  DMS parser  TRR parser sub argument)

Fixes Issue 1331 This handles the case where number of items is exactly divisible by number of items per line. Previously the code would always round up  where instead it should only round up when not exactly divisible.

removed ALL deprecated and legacy code: OLD CODE MIGHT BREAK - AtomGroup._atoms removed - AtomGroup.principleAxes (Issue 33) - DCD.DCDReader.dcd_header() and DCD.DCDWriter.dcd_header()   (use _dcd_header()) - Universe.dcd (and Universe.xtc  Universe.trr...) --- from   now on only Universe.trajectory is supported.   WILL BREAK LEGACY CODE! - removed the following packages from top-level MDAnalysis   name space: - AtomGroup  Selection: import them from MDAnalysis.core if   really needed (e.g. 'import MDAnalysis.core.AtomGroup') - distances  rms_fitting: 'import MDAnalysis.analysis.distances'   or 'import MDAnalysis.analysis.align.rms_fitting' (the   actual modules still live in MDAnalysis.core but they   might get moved in the future and bundled with   transformations) - 'from MDAnalysis import *' will only get ['Timeseries'    'Universe'  'asUniverse'  'Writer'  'collection'] - removed copy flag from distance_array and self_distance_array:   setting it to False would always give wrong results so there was   no good reason keeping it around (also removed the test cases with   known failures)

The Makefile in /doc/sphinx/ has been modified to put all output in the doc/html/ folder. Simply use the command: 'make html'. Newly included sphinx .rst documentation (source only  not including built html): -modules in /MDAnalysis/core/

coordinate tests: make sure that for Gromacs tests the conversion flag is set correctly - set core.flags[convert_gromacs_lengths] explicitly in setUp - encountered failures (possibly when running multiple tests with --processes=8) which   came about because the conversion flag was set to False even though it should have   been True

FIXED Issue 37: simulation box were not converted - added coordinates.core.triclinic_box() and triclinic_vectors() to handle conversion - added function convert_dimensions_to_unitcell() to Writers   and added to the requirements of the Trajectory API - GROWriter: introduced a temporary GROWriterStandard class which will replace the current   GROWriter (which got a DeprecationWarning)
Make topology pass tests in python 3 (#1436)

AtomGroup.coordinates() returns a VIEW on the array if it can (copy=False)  the copy=True hack was supposed to help with the old distance array bug but this has been fixed independently. I don't think that we need copy=True here but perhaps one should proceed with some caution. For testing the argument is left in the method.
removed conditional skipping of tests when scipy or matplotlib are missing
